CSC449 has the course title "Machine Vision". CSC449 is a 4.0 credit course taught by Chenliang Xu. CSC449 is offered every "Summer Spring Fall ". Introduction to computer vision, including camera models, basic image processing, pattern and object recognition, and elements of human vision. Specific topics include geometric issues, statistical models, Hough transforms, color theory, texture, and optic flow. CSC449, a graduate-level course, requires additional readings and assignments.Prerequisites: MATH161 and CSC242; MATH165 strongly recommended